post_text: Any high school students who have not picked up your schedules – you MUST do so next Monday-Wednesday. To get your schedule, you need to return your emergency form and device agreement (those were mailed home, but we have extras if needed), and you will also need to sign a COVID letter upon pickup. The HS office will be available for this Monday and Tuesday from 8-2, and Wednesday from 8-6. All students MUST complete this process to be prepared to have their schedules for our first day on September 8. We look forward to seeing you!

With sadness in my heart I am posting this announcement from the MHSAA. We will continue to keep our students updated as more information comes.

Dear MHSAA Community,

Earlier today, the Representative Council made the difficult decision to postpone football until the spring of 2021. This decision was based on feedback and input from the Governor’s office, state health department officials, member schools, collegiate conferences and individuals on both sides of the issue. Plans will be shared soon regarding allowed fall coach-player workouts as well as concepts for the spring football season dates, format and playoffs.

Know that all other fall sports in the low and moderate risk categories…

• Thursday, August 13th 8am-8pm
• Friday, August 14th 8am-5pm
• Monday, August 17th 8am-8pm

Thank you! Go Railroaders!

post_text:
Attention Families:

If you or someone you know still needs to register for kindergarten, please send an email to rcawson@durand.k12.mi.us as soon as possible. Return to school planning is occurring and enrollment is a big factor in all of it. Currently, kindergarten will be offered online and in person depending on family needs. So, if you are thinking to keep your kindergarten student home, we can still provide them with one of our talented kindergarten teachers virtually! We appreciate you helping us spread the word. In addition, the office has been contacting and responding to families who have questions or have registered their child for preschool or kindergarten. There are many more contacts to be made so we appreciate your patience! If you have any questions, submit them here and we will get back to you.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1_qi7dqN1hRVvCqDubbjGc0Bjqgp773xu5Ovnq1EuJCw/edit

post_text:
Seniors and families: Tomorrow’s graduation plan is still in place. Seniors will meet behind the HS gym at 6:30. Wear your caps and gowns, and you must also wear a mask and observe the 6-foot social distancing requirement. We will record the ceremony and make that available at a later date.

Two guests per graduate may enter the stadium. Guests must wear masks and observe 6-foot social distancing requirements as well. To make this easier, both the home and away bleachers will be open, and guests can enter through either gate.

The weather looks promising, but if there is a weather issue, we do have a back-up plan. In any case, you WILL receive your diplomas tomorrow!

Thank you for your patience with graduation. We plan to make tomorrow’s ceremony safe and special for you!

Two guests per graduate may enter the stadium. Guests must wear masks and observe 6-foot social distancing requirements as well. To make this easier, both the home and away bleachers will be open, and guests can enter through either gate.

Class of 2020 Students and Families,
This is Mrs. Knapp and I want to apologize for the late message (I attempted to call but the system would not let me after 9pm nor will it let me send an email to you), but WE HEAR YOU and are acting! At this time, we are going to go back to the drawing board to do what is best for the BEST group of kids out there-the Durand High School Class of 2020! Know that we are pausing our current plan. In the next few days, we will reach out and gather even more information and develop a new plan.

Thank you for your support and understanding!
Mrs. Knapp

post_text:
Dear Fellow Railroaders,
I hope this letter finds you and your family doing well and looking forward to some normalcy of summer. Needless to say, this spring has been very interesting and certainly a challenge in a number of ways. It seems though in the last couple of weeks I have sensed an uplifting spirit and Governor Whitmer's relaxation of restrictions only added to that feel on Monday. Suddenly more opportunities are available and the timing is right to share some plans that have long been in the works by the administrative team, as well as share some plans made in just the last two days. I'll simply list and explain each area below, but please know things will be evolving quickly in the next several weeks so I'll be able to communicate real information as we complete plans or are given guidance from MDE and the Governor's office. Your building principals will also continue to communicate as things evolve.

Read More Here: https://4.files.edl.io/9318/06/04/20/005846-19a7f23c-af08-43cf-8fc4-aa77a33fc2bb.pdf

Attention Durand Families! There will be another 25# produce box distribution on Friday, June 5th at Durand High School at 11:30. It’s first come, first serve. I apologize to those that did not receive a box today. I made a request for our distributor to double our delivery so hopefully families that didn’t receive one today will get one on the 5th. Please use the access drive off Lansing Road to form the line. Stay in your vehicles and the food service staff will place the box in your trunk. Also due to the high demand, we will be limiting one box per vehicle. You are welcome to go through the line a second time if you have more than one family in the vehicle but we want to give everyone the opportunity to get at least one box. If you have questions please call Lisa Beardsley, the food service director at 989-288-8703.

💙🚙🚒 CLASS OF 2020🚓🚜💙

It’s time (and we REALLY mean it) for the Second Annual Senior Parade! The city of Durand has altered their flyer and reinstated their plan for holding the senior parade again this year to honor our seniors, BUT with some VERY IMPORTANT AND MANDATORY proper social distancing parameters! Line up will begin at 6:30pm on Thursday, May 21st, 2020, with parade beginning at 7pm. Please see the attached flyer. We want this to be a safe, fun, and memorable experience for a VERY deserving group of young men and lady railroaders! Go Blue, Go White! 💙🎓🚂.

🚂🎼🎹 Congrats Durand Choir 🎹🎼🚂

Congrats all our Durand Choir students who performed at District Choral Festival yesterday and today. ALL THREE GROUPS- 8th Grade Choir, Varsity Choir, and Madrigals- received Division I ratings from ALL judges. They truly showed what it means to be a Railroader with their exemplary performances and musicality. All our singers will showcase what they’ve worked on for competition season in their Festival Concert, which is tomorrow evening on the HS stage at 6:30PM.

It’s a great day to be part of the Durand choir family. GO RAILROADERS! Congrats Ms. Delay and all the singers!

post_text:
🚂🌾 🐝 CONGRATS DHS FFA 📱🌱🚂

Congratulations to the State qualifying FFA demonstration team of Clara Henry, Olivia Ayers, Alanna Feldhouse and Aleshia Frederiksen. They competed in state semi finals yesterday morning and placed first moving on the the state finals today. This is an outstanding group of young ladies that have done an amazing job this year. Final results will be announced Friday morning. Congratulations to Abby Koenig and Maddy Botos for being recognized as the state winner in the Agriscience fair for their project entitled "The Negative Effects of Social Media on Agriculture". They are now eligible to submit their project to the national Agriscience fair hosted in late October in Indianapolis. Congrats ladies! A HUGE thank you to Mr. Birchmeier and Mrs. Wilson for their hours of dedication to our students!

Today at Intermission of the Michigan State vs. Iowa wrestling meet, former Durand High School coach Joe Guyski was honored for his contribution to the sport of wrestling, and to MSU and especially to the athletes he mentored over the years.
He was joined by his family, and as he came off the mat all he could say was “you have no idea what this means to me”.
Congrats Coach, you deserved this!

The students have worked very hard to earn a Certificate of Academic Excellence, or a first year award(an academic letter “D”), a two year award (honor pin), or a three year award (academic lamp pin). 🚂❤️💃🏼 2019 DHS PROM 🕺🏻❤️🚂

The 2019 Durand prom was a BIG hit. Lovett Hall in Dearborn was beautiful, and students had a great time dancing the night away in the historic building. Shoutout to our students, who were courteous, well-behaved, and kind the entire night. They made the chaperones who attended very proud to be Railroaders! Thank you to everyone who helped with making prom such a huge success! Congrats to our Prom Queen, Anna Church & our Prom King, Devyne Hazelwood.

🚂DHS Students Making a Difference🚂

Our DHS Teacher, Mrs. Salfate, recently received a grant from the King Arthur Flour Company of 100 pounds of flour, yeast, and bread bags. This gave the Nutrition and Foods II students the opportunity to bake over 200 rolls from scratch that were donated to the Carriage Town Ministries of Flint. The rolls were served at the shelter to over 100 people. The students also have used the donated flour to make pretzels, pizza and other bake goods. Thank you Mrs. Salfate and students for all you do!

post_text:
❤️🏆 CONGRATS DHS Robotics 🤖🚂

The Durand High School Railroader's Competive Robotics Team qualified for the Michigan State Championships after competing at LSSU this weekend! They are bringing back multiple awards from the event. These include the Pit Safety Award, the Gracious Professionalism Award, and Mrs. Shankster was nominated for the Woodie Flowers Award. This will be the first time for the robotics team to compete at States, which will take place this coming week at SVSU.
Congrats to Mr. & Mrs. Shankster, the mentors, & the entire team....ALL of your hard work and dedication is paying off and being recognized!

🏆🚂📚 CONGRATS! ✏️📓🏆

🏆🚂📚 CONGRATS! ✏️📓🏆

Congratulations to our Class of 2023 Shiawassee Scholars! Sydney Leydig, Jillian Reddy, & Jaxon Smith are the newest inductees into the Shiawassee Scholars program. These three students scored within the top 49 highest SAT scores among their peers in the county. We are EXTREMELY proud of you!!! #itsbettertobeblue
Congratulations to our robotics team for taking 2nd place at districts at Kettering! They also won the Judge's award and the Pit Safety Award.
